  "body": "# Allow user to format text through composer\r\n\r\n| As a user\r\n\r\n| I want to be able to format text through the compose\r\n\r\n| So that I donâ€™t have to learn markdown\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIf a user clicks on the formatting icon in the composer, it should show a list of available text formatting modes.\r\n\r\nIf the user clicks on any of the markdown icons, it should toggle the relative markdown  (i.e ** for bold for example)) and be selected. \r\n\r\nIf the user clicks on a toggled markdown icon, it should toggle it back to normal mode.\r\n\r\nCombinations should be allowed where it makes sense and where is not limited by performance (please check what we currently limit already). Block modes (i.e code blocks for example), cannot be nested in inline modes.\r\n\r\n### Designs\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/wA8Epdki2OWa8Vr067PCNQ/Composer-for-Mobile?node-id=2630%3A207636",
